WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.485 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:02.485 --> 00:00:04.473 align:middle line:90%


00:00:04.473 --> 00:00:07.649 align:middle line:90%
[AUDIO LOGO]

00:00:07.649 --> 00:00:08.449 align:middle line:90%


00:00:08.449 --> 00:00:11.928 align:middle line:90%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:11.928 --> 00:00:18.455 align:middle line:90%


00:00:18.455 --> 00:00:20.330 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA MEREDITH: I'm
preaching to the choir

00:00:20.330 --> 00:00:23.520 align:middle line:10%
when I tell you that the web
can be a dangerous place,

00:00:23.520 --> 00:00:27.110 align:middle line:10%
but I had no idea how
dangerous until I watched a Ted

00:00:27.110 --> 00:00:30.860 align:middle line:10%
Talk by our guest today, Alan
Pearce, author of The Sherlock

00:00:30.860 --> 00:00:33.030 align:middle line:10%
Holmes Handbook for
the Digital Age.

00:00:33.030 --> 00:00:35.720 align:middle line:10%
I learned that for
roughly $400, someone

00:00:35.720 --> 00:00:38.310 align:middle line:10%
can be paid to ruin
your entire life.

00:00:38.310 --> 00:00:39.960 align:middle line:84%
I think we need to
pay attention here.

00:00:39.960 --> 00:00:44.160 align:middle line:84%
And Alan, thank you so
much for writing this book,

00:00:44.160 --> 00:00:48.600 align:middle line:84%
and I'm glad I stumbled across
this Ted Talk initially.

00:00:48.600 --> 00:00:52.340 align:middle line:84%
And I was actually
horrified by a lot

00:00:52.340 --> 00:00:54.780 align:middle line:84%
of what you were saying because
we're innocently using it.

00:00:54.780 --> 00:00:58.410 align:middle line:84%
And I think most people think,
oh, we're innocently using it.

00:00:58.410 --> 00:01:00.430 align:middle line:84%
None of this will
ever affect us.

00:01:00.430 --> 00:01:02.830 align:middle line:84%
However, that's not
necessarily true.

00:01:02.830 --> 00:01:06.940 align:middle line:84%
But before any of that, I'd
like to go into your background,

00:01:06.940 --> 00:01:08.380 align:middle line:90%
you're a hardcore journalist.

00:01:08.380 --> 00:01:09.670 align:middle line:90%
You've been in war zones.

00:01:09.670 --> 00:01:11.610 align:middle line:84%
I want you to tell
us what kind of life

00:01:11.610 --> 00:01:13.750 align:middle line:84%
you had as a journalist
in the field.

00:01:13.750 --> 00:01:16.680 align:middle line:84%
And I know you've been up
against some horrendous

00:01:16.680 --> 00:01:18.480 align:middle line:90%
situations yourself.

00:01:18.480 --> 00:01:20.620 align:middle line:84%
>>ALAN PEARCE: Yeah,
it's a funny business.

00:01:20.620 --> 00:01:22.450 align:middle line:10%
I don't like to say
war correspondent.

00:01:22.450 --> 00:01:24.430 align:middle line:10%
I like to say Foreign
Affairs specialist.

00:01:24.430 --> 00:01:27.130 align:middle line:10%
And I found myself
in Afghanistan.

00:01:27.130 --> 00:01:29.950 align:middle line:84%
I'd been covering wars for
years, mostly in Southeast Asia.

00:01:29.950 --> 00:01:32.560 align:middle line:84%
I'd covered the Khmer Rouge war
in Cambodia for a long time.

00:01:32.560 --> 00:01:33.940 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Oh, you've been
doing this for a long time.

00:01:33.940 --> 00:01:34.450 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: Oh, yeah,
for a long time.

00:01:34.450 --> 00:01:35.760 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: When did
you start your--

00:01:35.760 --> 00:01:37.660 align:middle line:84%
when did your career
start, as a young pup?

00:01:37.660 --> 00:01:40.840 align:middle line:10%
>>PEARCE: No, funnily enough,
probably in my very late 20s,

00:01:40.840 --> 00:01:42.510 align:middle line:10%
early 30s.

00:01:42.510 --> 00:01:43.510 align:middle line:10%
You just stumbled on it.

00:01:43.510 --> 00:01:46.550 align:middle line:10%
I don't think a lot of people
choose to go to war, per se.

00:01:46.550 --> 00:01:47.350 align:middle line:90%
It happens.

00:01:47.350 --> 00:01:48.767 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: No, how
did you end up--

00:01:48.767 --> 00:01:50.670 align:middle line:84%
OK, were you studying
Pol Pot at the time?

00:01:50.670 --> 00:01:50.920 align:middle line:90%
Or--

00:01:50.920 --> 00:01:53.045 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: Well, I actually
found myself in Thailand

00:01:53.045 --> 00:01:55.028 align:middle line:84%
on a kind of free
vacation, and I

00:01:55.028 --> 00:01:56.320 align:middle line:90%
didn't want to go to the beach.

00:01:56.320 --> 00:01:57.987 align:middle line:84%
So I thought I'd go
to the refugee camps

00:01:57.987 --> 00:01:59.420 align:middle line:90%
on the Thai-Cambodian border.

00:01:59.420 --> 00:02:00.570 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: As one
does on vacation.

00:02:00.570 --> 00:02:01.403 align:middle line:90%
>>PEARCE: Of course.

00:02:01.403 --> 00:02:03.430 align:middle line:84%
And I found myself
getting hooked, as you do.

00:02:03.430 --> 00:02:05.930 align:middle line:84%
People's stories-- they
were just so fascinating.

00:02:05.930 --> 00:02:08.830 align:middle line:84%
So I spent some time trying
to get inside to Cambodia

00:02:08.830 --> 00:02:11.450 align:middle line:84%
with the different resistance
groups and managed to do that.

00:02:11.450 --> 00:02:14.560 align:middle line:84%
And then in time,
the Khmer Rouge

00:02:14.560 --> 00:02:16.240 align:middle line:84%
were kicked out
by the Vietnamese.

00:02:16.240 --> 00:02:18.020 align:middle line:84%
And the Vietnamese
were in control.

00:02:18.020 --> 00:02:20.680 align:middle line:10%
And when they left, I
was the first journalist

00:02:20.680 --> 00:02:22.150 align:middle line:10%
I'm aware of that
based themselves

00:02:22.150 --> 00:02:25.070 align:middle line:10%
in the capital, Phnom Penh,
which was like a ghost town.

00:02:25.070 --> 00:02:26.570 align:middle line:90%
It was beyond scary.

00:02:26.570 --> 00:02:30.920 align:middle line:84%
And so I did that for a long
time, that sort of thing.

00:02:30.920 --> 00:02:33.970 align:middle line:84%
And I covered the war, going
out with government forces,

00:02:33.970 --> 00:02:35.860 align:middle line:84%
and then when the United
Nations turned up,

00:02:35.860 --> 00:02:39.460 align:middle line:84%
going out with different
UN units and so on.

00:02:39.460 --> 00:02:40.770 align:middle line:90%
It becomes a way of life.

00:02:40.770 --> 00:02:41.570 align:middle line:90%
It just--

00:02:41.570 --> 00:02:42.010 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Sure.

00:02:42.010 --> 00:02:43.340 align:middle line:90%
Well, you were born to do it.

00:02:43.340 --> 00:02:45.520 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: Well,
here's the thing,

00:02:45.520 --> 00:02:47.810 align:middle line:84%
if you're doing that
in any given day,

00:02:47.810 --> 00:02:50.030 align:middle line:84%
you see the very
worst in humanity.

00:02:50.030 --> 00:02:52.700 align:middle line:84%
And you also see the very best
in humanity if you're lucky.

00:02:52.700 --> 00:02:53.500 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:02:53.500 --> 00:02:57.970 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: Yeah, you meet
the most wonderful people,

00:02:57.970 --> 00:02:59.290 align:middle line:90%
brave people.

00:02:59.290 --> 00:03:01.600 align:middle line:84%
I came out with post-traumatic
stress disorder,

00:03:01.600 --> 00:03:02.470 align:middle line:90%
so an awful lot do.

00:03:02.470 --> 00:03:04.777 align:middle line:84%
And what gets me is
kindness and bravery.

00:03:04.777 --> 00:03:07.110 align:middle line:84%
If I'm watching a movie, it's
got kindness and bravery--

00:03:07.110 --> 00:03:08.200 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, you're in tears.

00:03:08.200 --> 00:03:08.850 align:middle line:90%
>>PEARCE: --I'm in tears.

00:03:08.850 --> 00:03:09.970 align:middle line:90%
I have to hide my face.

00:03:09.970 --> 00:03:12.850 align:middle line:84%
And I know a lot of soldiers
find themselves doing this now.

00:03:12.850 --> 00:03:13.650 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:03:13.650 --> 00:03:15.832 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: Kindness and
bravery gets me every time.

00:03:15.832 --> 00:03:17.790 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Because you've
witnessed it firsthand

00:03:17.790 --> 00:03:18.743 align:middle line:90%
in extreme circumstances.

00:03:18.743 --> 00:03:19.543 align:middle line:90%
>>PEARCE: Yeah.

00:03:19.543 --> 00:03:21.593 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So you moved
out of Southeast Asia.

00:03:21.593 --> 00:03:23.260 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: Yeah, I
just stopped doing it.

00:03:23.260 --> 00:03:25.860 align:middle line:84%
I didn't get injured or
anything at that time.

00:03:25.860 --> 00:03:27.010 align:middle line:90%
I go back to London.

00:03:27.010 --> 00:03:29.510 align:middle line:84%
I'm working on the desk at the
BBC, and I'm getting bored.

00:03:29.510 --> 00:03:30.310 align:middle line:90%
I'm getting bored.

00:03:30.310 --> 00:03:31.980 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: What did
they have working on?

00:03:31.980 --> 00:03:33.397 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: Well, I
was just doing--

00:03:33.397 --> 00:03:35.260 align:middle line:84%
I was working on the
Southeast Asia desk,

00:03:35.260 --> 00:03:37.170 align:middle line:84%
and I'm just writing
news bulletins

00:03:37.170 --> 00:03:38.590 align:middle line:90%
and so on and so forth.

00:03:38.590 --> 00:03:39.790 align:middle line:90%
And it's OK.

00:03:39.790 --> 00:03:41.380 align:middle line:84%
I kind of like it,
but not as much.

00:03:41.380 --> 00:03:42.130 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You're a field guy.

00:03:42.130 --> 00:03:43.463 align:middle line:90%
>>PEARCE: Yes, I shouldn't stop.

00:03:43.463 --> 00:03:47.772 align:middle line:84%
So the post of Afghanistan came
up, the Kabul correspondent,

00:03:47.772 --> 00:03:50.230 align:middle line:84%
which was supposed to be the
most dangerous place on Earth.

00:03:50.230 --> 00:03:51.160 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Kabul, yes.

00:03:51.160 --> 00:03:52.510 align:middle line:90%
>>PEARCE: This is '96.

00:03:52.510 --> 00:03:55.090 align:middle line:84%
This is the first time
the Taliban took over.

00:03:55.090 --> 00:03:58.180 align:middle line:84%
So I arrived directly
into a siege.

00:03:58.180 --> 00:04:02.020 align:middle line:84%
I spent 10 months under Taliban
siege, being shelled every day.

00:04:02.020 --> 00:04:05.280 align:middle line:90%
And it was beyond grisly.

00:04:05.280 --> 00:04:10.272 align:middle line:84%
I mean, just beyond anything you
could ever imagine, the sadness.

00:04:10.272 --> 00:04:12.520 align:middle line:84%
Wherever you go,
something will happen.

00:04:12.520 --> 00:04:15.660 align:middle line:84%
A stick of rockets will
hit an apartment block,

00:04:15.660 --> 00:04:17.410 align:middle line:84%
and there'd be a whole
bunch of dead kids.

00:04:17.410 --> 00:04:19.740 align:middle line:84%
Or people are queuing
for water at a pump,

00:04:19.740 --> 00:04:22.300 align:middle line:84%
and mortars come
in and kill them.

00:04:22.300 --> 00:04:23.100 align:middle line:90%
And--

00:04:23.100 --> 00:04:24.450 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, what
was your protection

00:04:24.450 --> 00:04:25.510 align:middle line:90%
as a foreign journalist?

00:04:25.510 --> 00:04:26.620 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: Oh, there's
no protection.

00:04:26.620 --> 00:04:28.370 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So you just
go at your own risk.

00:04:28.370 --> 00:04:29.890 align:middle line:84%
They just say, go
at your own risk.

00:04:29.890 --> 00:04:31.060 align:middle line:90%
And was this for the BBC?

00:04:31.060 --> 00:04:31.990 align:middle line:90%
>>PEARCE: This for the BBC.

00:04:31.990 --> 00:04:33.115 align:middle line:90%
But that's how I prefer it.

00:04:33.115 --> 00:04:35.400 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't want an armed
guard, because how am I

00:04:35.400 --> 00:04:37.540 align:middle line:84%
going to talk to people
if I got a guy with an AK?

00:04:37.540 --> 00:04:39.010 align:middle line:90%
It's not going to work.

00:04:39.010 --> 00:04:42.900 align:middle line:84%
So anyway, I was enjoying it,
but it was horribly tense.

00:04:42.900 --> 00:04:46.720 align:middle line:84%
And I was losing weight,
and I wasn't eating well.

00:04:46.720 --> 00:04:48.390 align:middle line:84%
And I kept catching
various diseases

00:04:48.390 --> 00:04:50.620 align:middle line:84%
because the water wasn't
purified or anything.

00:04:50.620 --> 00:04:53.340 align:middle line:84%
So I had about six or
seven intestinal diseases

00:04:53.340 --> 00:04:55.420 align:middle line:90%
by the time I got out.

00:04:55.420 --> 00:04:57.520 align:middle line:90%
Anyway, the Taliban took over.

00:04:57.520 --> 00:05:00.170 align:middle line:90%
And so there we are.

00:05:00.170 --> 00:05:03.020 align:middle line:84%
Because it became a
reasonably large story,

00:05:03.020 --> 00:05:04.450 align:middle line:84%
there was quite
a few journalists

00:05:04.450 --> 00:05:06.550 align:middle line:90%
at this first press conference.

00:05:06.550 --> 00:05:09.380 align:middle line:84%
The guy says, we have
two major announcements.

00:05:09.380 --> 00:05:12.050 align:middle line:84%
One, we declare
Afghanistan an Emirate.

00:05:12.050 --> 00:05:15.940 align:middle line:84%
And the second thing
we want to tell you

00:05:15.940 --> 00:05:18.950 align:middle line:84%
is that we sentenced the
BBC correspondent to death.

00:05:18.950 --> 00:05:21.470 align:middle line:84%
And I was sitting there in
my chair and waiting for--

00:05:21.470 --> 00:05:23.510 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Were you the
only BBC correspondent?

00:05:23.510 --> 00:05:24.830 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: I'm the only
BBC correspondent.

00:05:24.830 --> 00:05:26.350 align:middle line:84%
So I'm sitting in
this chair, and I'm

00:05:26.350 --> 00:05:28.330 align:middle line:84%
waiting for someone to come
and lift me out of the chair

00:05:28.330 --> 00:05:29.240 align:middle line:90%
and take me away.

00:05:29.240 --> 00:05:30.040 align:middle line:90%
And they don't.

00:05:30.040 --> 00:05:32.690 align:middle line:84%
So I go back to the
office, and I call London.

00:05:32.690 --> 00:05:35.050 align:middle line:84%
And I say, hey, guys, I've
just been sentenced to death.

00:05:35.050 --> 00:05:37.700 align:middle line:84%
Oh, Alan, you don't
need worry about that.

00:05:37.700 --> 00:05:40.280 align:middle line:84%
So I'm thinking, that
doesn't seem right.

00:05:40.280 --> 00:05:45.190 align:middle line:84%
Anyway, I carried on for about
three weeks, and part of the job

00:05:45.190 --> 00:05:48.340 align:middle line:84%
used to be crossing the front
lines from government forces

00:05:48.340 --> 00:05:49.220 align:middle line:90%
to Taliban.

00:05:49.220 --> 00:05:51.440 align:middle line:84%
Now it was Taliban
to government forces.

00:05:51.440 --> 00:05:53.490 align:middle line:84%
So we're trying to
cross the front lines,

00:05:53.490 --> 00:05:56.850 align:middle line:84%
and we come up against
a Taliban checkpoint.

00:05:56.850 --> 00:05:58.630 align:middle line:90%
And they are beyond jumpy.

00:05:58.630 --> 00:06:00.610 align:middle line:84%
They've obviously been
in action that day.

00:06:00.610 --> 00:06:03.190 align:middle line:84%
They're probably all stoned,
looking at their eyes.

00:06:03.190 --> 00:06:05.890 align:middle line:84%
And I said to the driver,
let's get out of here.

00:06:05.890 --> 00:06:07.320 align:middle line:90%
We'd take another route.

00:06:07.320 --> 00:06:09.698 align:middle line:84%
Instead of putting the
Land Rover into reverse,

00:06:09.698 --> 00:06:12.240 align:middle line:84%
he put it into first gear and
drove straight into two Taliban

00:06:12.240 --> 00:06:13.050 align:middle line:90%
and knocked them over.

00:06:13.050 --> 00:06:13.860 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Uh, oh.

00:06:13.860 --> 00:06:14.820 align:middle line:90%
>>PEARCE: They got up.

00:06:14.820 --> 00:06:17.225 align:middle line:84%
Kindly, they didn't start
spraying us with their AKs.

00:06:17.225 --> 00:06:18.600 align:middle line:84%
They just beat in
the windscreen.

00:06:18.600 --> 00:06:20.620 align:middle line:90%
And my door gets yanked open.

00:06:20.620 --> 00:06:21.540 align:middle line:90%
I'm pulled out.

00:06:21.540 --> 00:06:26.050 align:middle line:84%
And this one-legged Mullah
comes along, and he's shouting.

00:06:26.050 --> 00:06:28.750 align:middle line:84%
Turns out he's
shouting, it's the BBC.

00:06:28.750 --> 00:06:30.210 align:middle line:90%
Kill them all.

00:06:30.210 --> 00:06:33.580 align:middle line:84%
And so they try and hang me,
but there weren't any trees.

00:06:33.580 --> 00:06:34.885 align:middle line:90%
So they throttled me.

00:06:34.885 --> 00:06:37.260 align:middle line:84%
[CHUCKLES] I was pinned up
against the side of the Landy,

00:06:37.260 --> 00:06:39.125 align:middle line:84%
and they throttled me
to unconsciousness.

00:06:39.125 --> 00:06:40.500 align:middle line:84%
They probably
thought I was dead.

00:06:40.500 --> 00:06:41.350 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: They did what to you?

00:06:41.350 --> 00:06:41.890 align:middle line:90%
>>PEARCE: Throttled me--

00:06:41.890 --> 00:06:42.210 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Throttled you.

00:06:42.210 --> 00:06:43.350 align:middle line:90%
>>PEARCE: --to unconsciousness.

00:06:43.350 --> 00:06:44.590 align:middle line:90%
But it's not like in a movie.

00:06:44.590 --> 00:06:46.420 align:middle line:90%
I'm not going like this.

00:06:46.420 --> 00:06:48.720 align:middle line:84%
It's just like-- I don't
know, like a Vulcan death grip

00:06:48.720 --> 00:06:50.290 align:middle line:90%
in Star Trek or something.

00:06:50.290 --> 00:06:51.670 align:middle line:90%
One minute I'm there.

00:06:51.670 --> 00:06:53.280 align:middle line:90%
The next it just goes black.

00:06:53.280 --> 00:06:56.770 align:middle line:84%
And then I woke up, came to
in the back of the Land Rover.

00:06:56.770 --> 00:06:57.910 align:middle line:90%
And we're driving away.

00:06:57.910 --> 00:07:00.940 align:middle line:84%
A commander had shown up, who
was a professional soldier.

00:07:00.940 --> 00:07:02.260 align:middle line:90%
He said, what are you doing?

00:07:02.260 --> 00:07:03.670 align:middle line:90%
Get this guy out of here.

00:07:03.670 --> 00:07:06.360 align:middle line:90%
And that was that.

00:07:06.360 --> 00:07:08.288 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know they'd
broken my neck.

00:07:08.288 --> 00:07:09.580 align:middle line:90%
I didn't know for three months.

00:07:09.580 --> 00:07:11.747 align:middle line:84%
This often happens to
professional football players,

00:07:11.747 --> 00:07:13.000 align:middle line:90%
rugby players, and so on.

00:07:13.000 --> 00:07:15.660 align:middle line:84%
I woke up three months later
not working for the BBC

00:07:15.660 --> 00:07:17.760 align:middle line:84%
anymore, because my
contract had expired.

00:07:17.760 --> 00:07:22.930 align:middle line:84%
And I couldn't move my arms,
and I was in diabolical pain.

00:07:22.930 --> 00:07:26.040 align:middle line:84%
So I spent about the
next couple of years--

00:07:26.040 --> 00:07:28.120 align:middle line:84%
semi-paralyzed is
an exaggeration,

00:07:28.120 --> 00:07:29.760 align:middle line:90%
but it was a bit like that.

00:07:29.760 --> 00:07:33.210 align:middle line:84%
This led me to getting involved
in the training of journalists

00:07:33.210 --> 00:07:36.390 align:middle line:84%
to operate in war zones,
the things you need to know

00:07:36.390 --> 00:07:39.150 align:middle line:84%
and you need to know a lot,
and an awful lot of journalists

00:07:39.150 --> 00:07:42.490 align:middle line:84%
will turn up not knowing, not
even knowing basic first aid,

00:07:42.490 --> 00:07:43.440 align:middle line:90%
for example.

00:07:43.440 --> 00:07:46.210 align:middle line:84%
Suppose you're with a colleague,
and they get shot in the chest.

00:07:46.210 --> 00:07:47.410 align:middle line:90%
What do you do about it?

00:07:47.410 --> 00:07:48.510 align:middle line:90%
They don't know.

00:07:48.510 --> 00:07:51.970 align:middle line:84%
Fortunately, the BBC
very kindly sent me

00:07:51.970 --> 00:07:53.660 align:middle line:90%
on a proper training course.

00:07:53.660 --> 00:07:57.310 align:middle line:84%
I'm a qualified battlefield
medic as a consequence of this,

00:07:57.310 --> 00:07:59.000 align:middle line:90%
and there's so much to know.

00:07:59.000 --> 00:08:00.620 align:middle line:84%
But mostly,
journalists don't know.

00:08:00.620 --> 00:08:03.010 align:middle line:84%
So a friend of mine set
up a training course

00:08:03.010 --> 00:08:06.035 align:middle line:84%
to train journalists,
and we got two SAS guys,

00:08:06.035 --> 00:08:06.910 align:middle line:90%
Special Air Service--

00:08:06.910 --> 00:08:07.710 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:08:07.710 --> 00:08:09.920 align:middle line:90%
>>PEARCE: --and the SAS doctor.

00:08:09.920 --> 00:08:14.900 align:middle line:84%
And he teaches battlefield
medical things,

00:08:14.900 --> 00:08:17.930 align:middle line:84%
but way beyond what the regular
infantry do, way beyond that.

00:08:17.930 --> 00:08:21.710 align:middle line:84%
And these guys taught us so
much in basically a weekend.

00:08:21.710 --> 00:08:22.510 align:middle line:90%
And--

00:08:22.510 --> 00:08:25.138 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Things you don't
learn in basic medic training.

00:08:25.138 --> 00:08:26.680 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: Not what
you would normally

00:08:26.680 --> 00:08:30.230 align:middle line:84%
learn, like stuff that would
make most people cringe.

00:08:30.230 --> 00:08:33.778 align:middle line:84%
I'm not doing that, but you
will do it to save a life.

00:08:33.778 --> 00:08:35.320 align:middle line:84%
After time-- because
I'm then getting

00:08:35.320 --> 00:08:36.940 align:middle line:84%
involved in this
training course,

00:08:36.940 --> 00:08:38.890 align:middle line:84%
and I'm giving talks
about this or that

00:08:38.890 --> 00:08:41.500 align:middle line:90%
and firearms and whatever.

00:08:41.500 --> 00:08:45.748 align:middle line:84%
And my wife, private
investigator, we

00:08:45.748 --> 00:08:47.540 align:middle line:84%
were having dinner with
one of her clients.

00:08:47.540 --> 00:08:49.350 align:middle line:84%
He's a former special
branch officer,

00:08:49.350 --> 00:08:50.880 align:middle line:90%
which is like the top end.

00:08:50.880 --> 00:08:53.880 align:middle line:84%
He was a former undercover
agent, and so forth.

00:08:53.880 --> 00:08:56.570 align:middle line:84%
And over dinner, he's telling
us about all the things

00:08:56.570 --> 00:08:58.800 align:middle line:84%
that they can't see
on the internet.

00:08:58.800 --> 00:09:01.160 align:middle line:84%
I'm thinking, oh,
yeah, like what?

00:09:01.160 --> 00:09:03.990 align:middle line:84%
I'm plugging him very gently,
and he twigs eventually.

00:09:03.990 --> 00:09:06.650 align:middle line:84%
But I'm sucking too much
information out of him,

00:09:06.650 --> 00:09:08.010 align:middle line:90%
and he just clams up.

00:09:08.010 --> 00:09:10.850 align:middle line:84%
But he told me enough that
I could go away and reverse

00:09:10.850 --> 00:09:12.030 align:middle line:90%
engineer it.

00:09:12.030 --> 00:09:16.620 align:middle line:84%
And I found out how journalists
can operate on the internet,

00:09:16.620 --> 00:09:20.150 align:middle line:84%
under the radar, how you can
communicate without people

00:09:20.150 --> 00:09:23.540 align:middle line:84%
intercepting your
communications, how

00:09:23.540 --> 00:09:26.390 align:middle line:84%
you can protect your
sources, for example.

00:09:26.390 --> 00:09:29.150 align:middle line:84%
Supposing you're in a
war zone, and you got

00:09:29.150 --> 00:09:31.070 align:middle line:90%
photographs of a mass grave.

00:09:31.070 --> 00:09:33.530 align:middle line:84%
How are you going to get
them out of the country?

00:09:33.530 --> 00:09:36.060 align:middle line:84%
Well, you can hide them
in all sorts of ways.

00:09:36.060 --> 00:09:38.460 align:middle line:84%
There's a wonderful thing
called steganography.

00:09:38.460 --> 00:09:41.060 align:middle line:84%
So let's say I've got a
whole bunch of photographs

00:09:41.060 --> 00:09:42.990 align:middle line:90%
of a mass grave.

00:09:42.990 --> 00:09:46.430 align:middle line:84%
I can put them inside,
say, a Britney Spears album

00:09:46.430 --> 00:09:47.800 align:middle line:90%
on my iPhone.

00:09:47.800 --> 00:09:51.040 align:middle line:84%
Hide it inside a particular
track or all the tracks,

00:09:51.040 --> 00:09:52.570 align:middle line:90%
one photograph inside the track.

00:09:52.570 --> 00:09:55.420 align:middle line:84%
Unless you've got prior
knowledge, you would never know.

00:09:55.420 --> 00:09:56.800 align:middle line:90%
You get out the other end.

00:09:56.800 --> 00:10:02.190 align:middle line:10%
You run the album through
a steganography program,

00:10:02.190 --> 00:10:03.910 align:middle line:10%
and out pop your photographs.

00:10:03.910 --> 00:10:04.862 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, my God.

00:10:04.862 --> 00:10:07.320 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: So I was teaching
journalists how to do all this.

00:10:07.320 --> 00:10:09.720 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Now, did you back
engineer it and figure it

00:10:09.720 --> 00:10:12.520 align:middle line:84%
out yourself, or did they give
you some hints of how to do it?

00:10:12.520 --> 00:10:15.090 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: He only gave me enough
to know that it can be done.

00:10:15.090 --> 00:10:17.310 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And that
they're doing it.

00:10:17.310 --> 00:10:18.180 align:middle line:90%
>>PEARCE: Yeah.

00:10:18.180 --> 00:10:20.980 align:middle line:84%
That took me a long time,
to find these things out.

00:10:20.980 --> 00:10:22.875 align:middle line:84%
And I found them for
a variety of ways.

00:10:22.875 --> 00:10:23.675 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:10:23.675 --> 00:10:24.900 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: Then I found,
there was a thing

00:10:24.900 --> 00:10:26.320 align:middle line:90%
called the Occupy Movement.

00:10:26.320 --> 00:10:27.903 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if
anyone remembers that.

00:10:27.903 --> 00:10:28.703 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, yeah.

00:10:28.703 --> 00:10:30.630 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: And I was
training their people how

00:10:30.630 --> 00:10:33.090 align:middle line:90%
to communicate under the radar.

00:10:33.090 --> 00:10:36.310 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, I can
write a book about this.

00:10:36.310 --> 00:10:38.800 align:middle line:84%
So I just started
writing a book,

00:10:38.800 --> 00:10:42.160 align:middle line:84%
and I wrote one book that had
everything in it, all of it.

00:10:42.160 --> 00:10:44.250 align:middle line:84%
And it occurred to
me that no one really

00:10:44.250 --> 00:10:46.890 align:middle line:84%
is ever going to buy a
cybersecurity handbook

00:10:46.890 --> 00:10:47.690 align:middle line:90%
and read it.

00:10:47.690 --> 00:10:49.130 align:middle line:90%
People just don't do that.

00:10:49.130 --> 00:10:51.760 align:middle line:10%
So I thought I would
write a Sherlock Holmes

00:10:51.760 --> 00:10:54.400 align:middle line:10%
story, the world's
best detective,

00:10:54.400 --> 00:10:58.760 align:middle line:10%
told through the words of
his sidekick, Dr. Watson.

00:10:58.760 --> 00:11:01.070 align:middle line:84%
And it's a full-on
Sherlock Holmes story.

00:11:01.070 --> 00:11:02.660 align:middle line:84%
But when you get
to the end of it,

00:11:02.660 --> 00:11:07.390 align:middle line:84%
you realize you've absorbed
so much knowledge almost

00:11:07.390 --> 00:11:08.320 align:middle line:90%
by osmosis.

00:11:08.320 --> 00:11:09.170 align:middle line:90%
You don't know.

00:11:09.170 --> 00:11:11.380 align:middle line:84%
And you've just
had a fun journey.

00:11:11.380 --> 00:11:12.645 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, how fascinating.

00:11:12.645 --> 00:11:14.770 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: And show how to
hide things inside things

00:11:14.770 --> 00:11:17.650 align:middle line:90%
and how to communicate.

00:11:17.650 --> 00:11:20.560 align:middle line:84%
Like, for example,
the FBI or whoever

00:11:20.560 --> 00:11:23.920 align:middle line:84%
will be monitoring people's
emails or their WhatsApp

00:11:23.920 --> 00:11:26.210 align:middle line:84%
if they can, even
though it's encrypted.

00:11:26.210 --> 00:11:27.610 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:11:27.610 --> 00:11:30.880 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: Crooks and terrorists
don't operate that way.

00:11:30.880 --> 00:11:34.700 align:middle line:84%
They would operate inside
things like World of Warcraft,

00:11:34.700 --> 00:11:38.328 align:middle line:84%
where you can, within the
game, you've got chat facility.

00:11:38.328 --> 00:11:40.120 align:middle line:84%
Now, if you're talking
about bombs and guns

00:11:40.120 --> 00:11:41.860 align:middle line:84%
within World of
Warcraft, that's not

00:11:41.860 --> 00:11:43.280 align:middle line:90%
going to ring the alarm bells.

00:11:43.280 --> 00:11:45.720 align:middle line:84%
So they will
communicate that way.

00:11:45.720 --> 00:11:48.770 align:middle line:84%
They might even communicate in
something like My Little Pony

00:11:48.770 --> 00:11:50.690 align:middle line:90%
World and talk in code.

00:11:50.690 --> 00:11:51.600 align:middle line:90%
And don't say "bomb."

00:11:51.600 --> 00:11:53.540 align:middle line:90%
Say "birthday cake," and so on.

00:11:53.540 --> 00:11:56.270 align:middle line:84%
So I was showing people
how you can do this.

00:11:56.270 --> 00:11:57.420 align:middle line:90%
[CHUCKLING]

00:11:57.420 --> 00:11:59.700 align:middle line:84%
So I'm taking all the
dark arts, as it were,

00:11:59.700 --> 00:12:02.510 align:middle line:84%
and I'm employing them for
the power of good, showing

00:12:02.510 --> 00:12:04.640 align:middle line:84%
journalists, and eventually
human rights lawyers,

00:12:04.640 --> 00:12:06.950 align:middle line:84%
how they can communicate
with their clients

00:12:06.950 --> 00:12:08.868 align:middle line:90%
and gather and retain--

00:12:08.868 --> 00:12:09.910 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Without being--

00:12:09.910 --> 00:12:10.550 align:middle line:90%
>>PEARCE: Without having--

00:12:10.550 --> 00:12:10.855 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: --surveilled.

00:12:10.855 --> 00:12:13.340 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: --someone
looking over your shoulder.

00:12:13.340 --> 00:12:15.620 align:middle line:84%
Because it's a complete
joke that we are all

00:12:15.620 --> 00:12:18.360 align:middle line:84%
being monitored all the time
by all-- because they do it

00:12:18.360 --> 00:12:19.220 align:middle line:90%
because they can.

00:12:19.220 --> 00:12:21.270 align:middle line:90%
And why wouldn't you if you can?

00:12:21.270 --> 00:12:24.530 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, but they're not really
going to gain anything by--

00:12:24.530 --> 00:12:26.300 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: What a massive waste.

00:12:26.300 --> 00:12:28.050 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: I mean,
reading my mom's emails.

00:12:28.050 --> 00:12:29.925 align:middle line:84%
I mean, what are they
going to get from that?

00:12:29.925 --> 00:12:30.942 align:middle line:90%
Nothing.

00:12:30.942 --> 00:12:31.775 align:middle line:90%
And the terrorists--

00:12:31.775 --> 00:12:33.245 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Bakewell
tart recipe, maybe.

00:12:33.245 --> 00:12:33.500 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:12:33.500 --> 00:12:34.770 align:middle line:90%
>>PEARCE: Yeah, exactly.

00:12:34.770 --> 00:12:37.670 align:middle line:84%
But the terrorists and the drug
dealers and the arms dealers

00:12:37.670 --> 00:12:40.550 align:middle line:84%
and all the rest of it, they're
using the dark web, which

00:12:40.550 --> 00:12:41.790 align:middle line:90%
is a part of the internet.

00:12:41.790 --> 00:12:44.140 align:middle line:84%
The internet-- I mean, if
you think of the internet,

00:12:44.140 --> 00:12:46.140 align:middle line:90%
think of an iceberg.

00:12:46.140 --> 00:12:49.890 align:middle line:84%
And the surface web, like
an iceberg, is what we use,

00:12:49.890 --> 00:12:52.030 align:middle line:84%
if you're using
Google or whatever.

00:12:52.030 --> 00:12:55.300 align:middle line:84%
They're really only indexing the
things people are interested in.

00:12:55.300 --> 00:12:57.940 align:middle line:84%
There's so much on the internet
that no one's interested in.

00:12:57.940 --> 00:12:58.900 align:middle line:90%
There's databases.

00:12:58.900 --> 00:13:00.067 align:middle line:90%
There's all sorts of things.

00:13:00.067 --> 00:13:01.420 align:middle line:90%
They don't search inside there.

00:13:01.420 --> 00:13:04.000 align:middle line:84%
So the internet is
like an iceberg.

00:13:04.000 --> 00:13:06.360 align:middle line:84%
You see what's above, but
there's a massive amount

00:13:06.360 --> 00:13:07.180 align:middle line:90%
underneath.

00:13:07.180 --> 00:13:10.950 align:middle line:84%
And within the massive amount
underneath are the dark webs.

00:13:10.950 --> 00:13:13.500 align:middle line:84%
I can't say how many there are,
because the whole nature is

00:13:13.500 --> 00:13:14.650 align:middle line:90%
that they're secret.

00:13:14.650 --> 00:13:16.150 align:middle line:84%
But there's one
we do know about,

00:13:16.150 --> 00:13:19.650 align:middle line:84%
which is the Tor network, which
is actually set up by the US

00:13:19.650 --> 00:13:22.530 align:middle line:84%
Navy way back as a means
for them to communicate

00:13:22.530 --> 00:13:24.720 align:middle line:84%
surreptitiously
amongst themselves.

00:13:24.720 --> 00:13:27.880 align:middle line:84%
That somehow got out into the
wild, into the real world,

00:13:27.880 --> 00:13:30.210 align:middle line:84%
and other people
started using it.

00:13:30.210 --> 00:13:32.830 align:middle line:84%
It's just like the
regular internet,

00:13:32.830 --> 00:13:34.710 align:middle line:84%
but it's a bit like
the old dial-up,

00:13:34.710 --> 00:13:36.490 align:middle line:84%
that it's all kind
of slow and clunky,

00:13:36.490 --> 00:13:38.010 align:middle line:84%
because what you're
doing, you're

00:13:38.010 --> 00:13:41.890 align:middle line:84%
not just you connecting at
home on your laptop direct

00:13:41.890 --> 00:13:42.770 align:middle line:90%
to a website.

00:13:42.770 --> 00:13:45.380 align:middle line:10%
You're going entirely
around the globe,

00:13:45.380 --> 00:13:48.650 align:middle line:10%
bouncing off different devices
all the way around the world,

00:13:48.650 --> 00:13:51.370 align:middle line:10%
so it's impossible to trace
you back to your source.

00:13:51.370 --> 00:13:53.680 align:middle line:84%
So it's all a bit
clunky and slow.

00:13:53.680 --> 00:13:56.990 align:middle line:84%
Once you're in there, if
I wanted to buy an AK-47,

00:13:56.990 --> 00:13:59.770 align:middle line:84%
for example, I
can do it so easy.

00:13:59.770 --> 00:14:01.450 align:middle line:84%
And the thing is,
people aren't going

00:14:01.450 --> 00:14:04.870 align:middle line:84%
to cheat you so much because
you use a system of escrow

00:14:04.870 --> 00:14:07.310 align:middle line:90%
where I want to buy an AK-47.

00:14:07.310 --> 00:14:08.870 align:middle line:90%
Let's say it's $500.

00:14:08.870 --> 00:14:12.890 align:middle line:84%
I put $500 into
escrow from a website.

00:14:12.890 --> 00:14:14.570 align:middle line:90%
That's the marketplace.

00:14:14.570 --> 00:14:17.360 align:middle line:84%
The dealer sends me the
AK, which, incidentally,

00:14:17.360 --> 00:14:18.820 align:middle line:84%
they break down
into parts and put

00:14:18.820 --> 00:14:21.832 align:middle line:84%
inside things like fax machines
and other bits of kit like that.

00:14:21.832 --> 00:14:23.540 align:middle line:84%
And then it arrives,
and you assemble it.

00:14:23.540 --> 00:14:27.700 align:middle line:84%
You look on YouTube, see how
to put together an AK-47.

00:14:27.700 --> 00:14:31.300 align:middle line:84%
And then you release the
money from escrow and so on.

00:14:31.300 --> 00:14:33.700 align:middle line:84%
Drug dealers work in
exactly the same way,

00:14:33.700 --> 00:14:36.430 align:middle line:84%
but the tools that they're
using are the tools

00:14:36.430 --> 00:14:38.710 align:middle line:84%
that I know that journalists
and human rights lawyers

00:14:38.710 --> 00:14:40.460 align:middle line:90%
could really be using.

00:14:40.460 --> 00:14:45.110 align:middle line:84%
And to be a journalist,
if I say my mom's emails

00:14:45.110 --> 00:14:46.755 align:middle line:84%
are being read, you
can bet your life,

00:14:46.755 --> 00:14:49.130 align:middle line:84%
if you're a proper journalist,
that they are watching you

00:14:49.130 --> 00:14:49.950 align:middle line:90%
everywhere.

00:14:49.950 --> 00:14:51.158 align:middle line:90%
Now, I don't just mean that--

00:14:51.158 --> 00:14:52.380 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: No, this is true.

00:14:52.380 --> 00:14:53.820 align:middle line:90%
>>PEARCE: But everywhere.

00:14:53.820 --> 00:14:54.620 align:middle line:90%
I't's every--

00:14:54.620 --> 00:14:55.700 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Every agency.

00:14:55.700 --> 00:14:56.867 align:middle line:90%
>>PEARCE: It goes like this.

00:14:56.867 --> 00:15:00.483 align:middle line:84%
You'd be stupid if you
didn't, so they do.

00:15:00.483 --> 00:15:01.650 align:middle line:90%
They will gather everything.

00:15:01.650 --> 00:15:03.420 align:middle line:84%
It's not like one person
is reading your emails.

00:15:03.420 --> 00:15:05.545 align:middle line:84%
It's a computer, and they're
looking for key words,

00:15:05.545 --> 00:15:08.275 align:middle line:84%
like "bomb" and so forth,
and "kill" and "president"

00:15:08.275 --> 00:15:09.150 align:middle line:90%
and things like that.

00:15:09.150 --> 00:15:11.438 align:middle line:84%
And if they all pop up
in the same message,

00:15:11.438 --> 00:15:12.980 align:middle line:84%
they'll come and
get you in some way.

00:15:12.980 --> 00:15:14.438 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You do
a funny little bit

00:15:14.438 --> 00:15:17.030 align:middle line:84%
about-- write this in
an email to someone,

00:15:17.030 --> 00:15:18.738 align:middle line:84%
sprinkle those words
through, and see

00:15:18.738 --> 00:15:20.030 align:middle line:90%
how quickly you get a reaction.

00:15:20.030 --> 00:15:20.850 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: --if you
don't believe me.

00:15:20.850 --> 00:15:21.450 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, yeah.

00:15:21.450 --> 00:15:22.650 align:middle line:84%
Next time, you
write to your mom.

00:15:22.650 --> 00:15:23.150 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: So--

00:15:23.150 --> 00:15:23.440 align:middle line:90%
>>PEARCE: Yeah.

00:15:23.440 --> 00:15:23.730 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:15:23.730 --> 00:15:25.480 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So I have a
couple of questions.

00:15:25.480 --> 00:15:28.040 align:middle line:84%
One of them is, you
were teaching this

00:15:28.040 --> 00:15:29.105 align:middle line:90%
openly or covertly?

00:15:29.105 --> 00:15:30.480 align:middle line:10%
>>PEARCE: Oh, no,
openly, openly.

00:15:30.480 --> 00:15:33.740 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, so did any
kind of governmental agencies

00:15:33.740 --> 00:15:34.800 align:middle line:90%
bother you at all?

00:15:34.800 --> 00:15:36.000 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: They don't
know what I'm teaching.

00:15:36.000 --> 00:15:38.000 align:middle line:84%
They're probably not
sending anyone on a course.

00:15:38.000 --> 00:15:41.590 align:middle line:84%
I mean, a bunch of journos
learning first aid,

00:15:41.590 --> 00:15:42.797 align:middle line:90%
learning about firearms.

00:15:42.797 --> 00:15:44.255 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So they
have no idea, OK.

00:15:44.255 --> 00:15:46.360 align:middle line:90%
And then what I wonder--

