00:37:40.240 --> 00:37:42.470 align:middle line:84%
Most people will say, well,
I have nothing to hide.

00:37:42.470 --> 00:37:43.460 align:middle line:90%
What difference does it make?

00:37:43.460 --> 00:37:44.377 align:middle line:90%
>>PEARCE: Yeah, right.

00:37:44.377 --> 00:37:47.710 align:middle line:84%
Well, this is a bit like
quoting the Nazis because Joseph

00:37:47.710 --> 00:37:50.510 align:middle line:84%
Goebbels coined the phrase
"if you have nothing to hide,

00:37:50.510 --> 00:37:53.363 align:middle line:84%
you have nothing to fear"
when he founded the Gestapo.

00:37:53.363 --> 00:37:54.280 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, right.

00:37:54.280 --> 00:37:55.655 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: Now, so
I don't like it

00:37:55.655 --> 00:37:58.185 align:middle line:84%
when people quote the Nazis
in terms of personal security.

00:37:58.185 --> 00:37:59.080 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But that's
most people say.

00:37:59.080 --> 00:38:01.000 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: That's
what most people say.

00:38:01.000 --> 00:38:04.300 align:middle line:84%
But then you look at
corporations or crooks

00:38:04.300 --> 00:38:05.410 align:middle line:90%
and stuff.

00:38:05.410 --> 00:38:07.535 align:middle line:84%
It's not about having to
hide things because you're

00:38:07.535 --> 00:38:08.790 align:middle line:90%
up to no good yourself.

00:38:08.790 --> 00:38:11.683 align:middle line:84%
If you were a journalist,
and you're trying to find,

00:38:11.683 --> 00:38:13.100 align:middle line:84%
I don't know, a
corporation that's

00:38:13.100 --> 00:38:16.530 align:middle line:84%
poisoning rivers or something,
that's a good thing.

00:38:16.530 --> 00:38:21.110 align:middle line:84%
And you're using these dark
arts for that power of good,

00:38:21.110 --> 00:38:21.960 align:middle line:90%
then use them.

00:38:21.960 --> 00:38:22.760 align:middle line:90%
Use them.

00:38:22.760 --> 00:38:25.250 align:middle line:84%
And I will show you every
way I have discovered,

00:38:25.250 --> 00:38:26.808 align:middle line:84%
and I've discovered
them from a--

00:38:26.808 --> 00:38:28.350 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: In a
Sherlock Holmes story.

00:38:28.350 --> 00:38:29.960 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: Well, yeah, that's why
I put them in a Sherlock Holmes

00:38:29.960 --> 00:38:31.610 align:middle line:84%
story, because no one's
going to sit and read

00:38:31.610 --> 00:38:32.820 align:middle line:90%
a cybersecurity handbook.

00:38:32.820 --> 00:38:33.653 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I love it.

00:38:33.653 --> 00:38:35.370 align:middle line:84%
OK, so I have a
question for you.

00:38:35.370 --> 00:38:38.990 align:middle line:84%
We have these events that
take place all the time.

00:38:38.990 --> 00:38:40.790 align:middle line:84%
Of course, depending
on the community

00:38:40.790 --> 00:38:44.360 align:middle line:84%
that you are logged
in with, some people

00:38:44.360 --> 00:38:47.637 align:middle line:84%
can say false flags, attacks,
Manchurian candidates,

00:38:47.637 --> 00:38:48.470 align:middle line:90%
and all of the like.

