then they write
about their history,

00:39:15.820 --> 00:39:20.770 align:middle line:10%
a 20-year-old who belongs to
a gun club, versus terrorists,

00:39:20.770 --> 00:39:23.260 align:middle line:10%
deep, deep terrorists
and, say, the Mossad,

00:39:23.260 --> 00:39:27.760 align:middle line:10%
which has agents embedded in
every terrorist organization,

00:39:27.760 --> 00:39:29.140 align:middle line:10%
including Hamas, to the hilt--

00:39:29.140 --> 00:39:30.970 align:middle line:10%
>>PEARCE: Because they'd be
foolish that they didn't.

00:39:30.970 --> 00:39:33.460 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, so yeah,
they've got agents everywhere.

00:39:33.460 --> 00:39:36.845 align:middle line:90%
They know what's going on.

00:39:36.845 --> 00:39:39.220 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: They don't need to
monitor us as a consequence.

00:39:39.220 --> 00:39:39.540 align:middle line:90%
They do--

00:39:39.540 --> 00:39:40.590 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's
what I'm asking you.

00:39:40.590 --> 00:39:41.680 align:middle line:90%
>>PEARCE: No, they do not.

00:39:41.680 --> 00:39:44.060 align:middle line:84%
They're doing it
for other reasons.

00:39:44.060 --> 00:39:45.460 align:middle line:90%
They want to know all sorts.

00:39:45.460 --> 00:39:46.877 align:middle line:84%
They just want to
know what you're

00:39:46.877 --> 00:39:48.330 align:middle line:90%
thinking on a basic level.

00:39:48.330 --> 00:39:52.800 align:middle line:84%
Because next time they're
having an election, they can--

00:39:52.800 --> 00:39:54.730 align:middle line:84%
their prospectus
for their election,

00:39:54.730 --> 00:39:58.230 align:middle line:84%
they can target it to suit what
people are thinking because they

00:39:58.230 --> 00:39:59.530 align:middle line:90%
know their deeper thoughts.

00:39:59.530 --> 00:39:59.980 align:middle line:90%
Well I'm sorry--

00:39:59.980 --> 00:40:00.450 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: And their fears.

00:40:00.450 --> 00:40:01.120 align:middle line:90%
>>PEARCE: --over my shoulder.

00:40:01.120 --> 00:40:01.870 align:middle line:90%
I don't like it.

00:40:01.870 --> 00:40:02.340 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:40:02.340 --> 00:40:03.750 align:middle line:84%
They know their
fears, and that's

00:40:03.750 --> 00:40:06.340 align:middle line:84%
how you're going to manipulate
the masses, because they then

00:40:06.340 --> 00:40:08.120 align:middle line:84%
control the media
in all countries,

00:40:08.120 --> 00:40:10.150 align:middle line:84%
not just this
country, all medias.

00:40:10.150 --> 00:40:11.920 align:middle line:84%
The intelligence
controls the media.

00:40:11.920 --> 00:40:14.620 align:middle line:84%
And if anybody doesn't think
so, they need to study--

00:40:14.620 --> 00:40:16.453 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: As a journalist
in the field, when

00:40:16.453 --> 00:40:19.270 align:middle line:84%
you bump into another
journalist, mostly for me

00:40:19.270 --> 00:40:21.078 align:middle line:84%
because I'm skeptical,
first thought

00:40:21.078 --> 00:40:22.120 align:middle line:90%
is, is that a journalist?

00:40:22.120 --> 00:40:23.930 align:middle line:84%
Or are they working
for an agency?

00:40:23.930 --> 00:40:25.090 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:40:25.090 --> 00:40:28.690 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: A very good friend
of mine, a photographer that I

00:40:28.690 --> 00:40:30.910 align:middle line:84%
worked with for
years, turned out

00:40:30.910 --> 00:40:34.810 align:middle line:84%
to be feeding
information to the Brits,

00:40:34.810 --> 00:40:39.610 align:middle line:84%
not as a spy or anything,
but as a sideline,

00:40:39.610 --> 00:40:42.740 align:middle line:84%
found out because we got caught
doing something together.

00:40:42.740 --> 00:40:47.500 align:middle line:84%
We caught the Thai soldiers
about to massacre some refugees.

00:40:47.500 --> 00:40:50.560 align:middle line:84%
His sources told us
to leave the country

00:40:50.560 --> 00:40:52.940 align:middle line:84%
because we were being charged,
and that's how we found--

00:40:52.940 --> 00:40:53.830 align:middle line:90%
I found out--

00:40:53.830 --> 00:40:55.880 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That he was
a plant, more or less.

00:40:55.880 --> 00:40:56.680 align:middle line:90%
>>PEARCE: Yeah.

00:40:56.680 --> 00:41:00.290 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So if you have the
lone shooter story, in general,

00:41:00.290 --> 00:41:04.130 align:middle line:84%
we're reading our headlines, oh,
19-year-old, 22-year-old male,

00:41:04.130 --> 00:41:05.930 align:middle line:90%
mentally disturbed.

00:41:05.930 --> 00:41:07.680 align:middle line:84%
Just your general
thought on this.

00:41:07.680 --> 00:41:09.560 align:middle line:84%
Are they generally
lone agent people

00:41:09.560 --> 00:41:12.510 align:middle line:84%
that do this that you couldn't
have monitored them per se?

00:41:12.510 --> 00:41:13.890 align:middle line:90%
They're not really that deep.

00:41:13.890 --> 00:41:16.432 align:middle line:90%
Or are they something more?

00:41:16.432 --> 00:41:18.890 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: Oftentimes, though,
you will go back and you will

00:41:18.890 --> 00:41:21.240 align:middle line:84%
see they've posted all
sorts of crazy stuff--

00:41:21.240 --> 00:41:22.950 align:middle line:90%
all sorts of crazy stuff.

00:41:22.950 --> 00:41:24.120 align:middle line:90%
But what do you do?

00:41:24.120 --> 00:41:25.890 align:middle line:90%
You then, you're into precrime.

00:41:25.890 --> 00:41:27.920 align:middle line:84%
It's like a Philip K.
Dick novel of something.

00:41:27.920 --> 00:41:28.770 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Minority Report, yeah?

00:41:28.770 --> 00:41:29.880 align:middle line:90%
>>PEARCE: Yeah, exactly.

00:41:29.880 --> 00:41:32.720 align:middle line:84%
So what, you arrest
people for precrime?

00:41:32.720 --> 00:41:33.890 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:41:33.890 --> 00:41:36.460 align:middle line:84%
And maybe they were doing it
just because they were angry

00:41:36.460 --> 00:41:37.260 align:middle line:90%
one day.

00:41:37.260 --> 00:41:37.470 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:41:37.470 --> 00:41:38.010 align:middle line:90%
>>PEARCE: That's it.

00:41:38.010 --> 00:41:40.040 align:middle line:84%
But they had no intention
of killing anyone.

00:41:40.040 --> 00:41:42.610 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But the ones
who do the real terrorism,

00:41:42.610 --> 00:41:44.110 align:middle line:84%
the one who manipulate
governments--

00:41:44.110 --> 00:41:44.660 align:middle line:90%
>>PEARCE: You won't find them.

00:41:44.660 --> 00:41:46.110 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You're not
going to ever find them.

00:41:46.110 --> 00:41:47.820 align:middle line:84%
They are at the base
of the deep web.

00:41:47.820 --> 00:41:49.528 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: And many
times they're not even

00:41:49.528 --> 00:41:51.510 align:middle line:90%
using that technology at all.

00:41:51.510 --> 00:41:54.740 align:middle line:84%
They've gone back to original
spy craft of handwritten notes

00:41:54.740 --> 00:41:59.480 align:middle line:84%
and suchlike, and codes, codes
based on a book, book code,

00:41:59.480 --> 00:42:00.502 align:middle line:90%
and so on and so forth.

00:42:00.502 --> 00:42:01.585 align:middle line:90%
They use those techniques.

00:42:01.585 --> 00:42:03.290 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Have you encountered
this sort of thing in your life?

00:42:03.290 --> 00:42:04.457 align:middle line:90%
>>PEARCE: No, because they--

00:42:04.457 --> 00:42:05.257 align:middle line:90%
[CHUCKLES]

00:42:05.257 --> 00:42:07.424 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: They would never
be encountered by someone

00:42:07.424 --> 00:42:08.420 align:middle line:90%
like you or anyone.

00:42:08.420 --> 00:42:10.003 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: If you're
really doing that,

00:42:10.003 --> 00:42:13.040 align:middle line:84%
you're using some spycraft that
people were using the 1800s.

00:42:13.040 --> 00:42:13.840 align:middle line:90%
Yeah?

00:42:13.840 --> 00:42:14.870 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And they've
gone back to that.

00:42:14.870 --> 00:42:15.850 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: Yeah, and they're
not going to find you,

00:42:15.850 --> 00:42:16.910 align:middle line:90%
because where they're looking?

00:42:16.910 --> 00:42:17.960 align:middle line:90%
They're looking online.

00:42:17.960 --> 00:42:19.340 align:middle line:84%
They're looking in your
mom's email account.

00:42:19.340 --> 00:42:22.280 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So the ones that are
really screwing up this planet,

00:42:22.280 --> 00:42:25.930 align:middle line:84%
really causing deep
societal disturbances,

00:42:25.930 --> 00:42:30.250 align:middle line:84%
creating wars, et cetera, those
are the ones that are never

00:42:30.250 --> 00:42:31.790 align:middle line:90%
going to be gotten to anyway.

00:42:31.790 --> 00:42:34.450 align:middle line:10%
And they're doing it often in
relationship to the governments

00:42:34.450 --> 00:42:36.080 align:middle line:10%
and the intelligence agencies.

00:42:36.080 --> 00:42:38.020 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: Because many times,
there's somebody even stronger

00:42:38.020 --> 00:42:38.780 align:middle line:90%
behind them.

00:42:38.780 --> 00:42:39.070 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:42:39.070 --> 00:42:40.940 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: Take the
Russians and the Chinese.

00:42:40.940 --> 00:42:43.450 align:middle line:84%
They're hacking left,
right, and center.

00:42:43.450 --> 00:42:46.270 align:middle line:84%
In Britain, where I
come from, now hospitals

00:42:46.270 --> 00:42:47.980 align:middle line:84%
are having these
ransomware attacks

00:42:47.980 --> 00:42:49.720 align:middle line:90%
where they lock the computers.

00:42:49.720 --> 00:42:52.133 align:middle line:84%
And you can't carry
out operations.

00:42:52.133 --> 00:42:53.300 align:middle line:90%
You can't book appointments.

00:42:53.300 --> 00:42:57.220 align:middle line:84%
You can't do anything unless
you pay millions of dollars

00:42:57.220 --> 00:42:59.770 align:middle line:84%
in Bitcoin to some
entity that's hiding

00:42:59.770 --> 00:43:03.050 align:middle line:84%
in Russia or China or
North Korea or wherever,

00:43:03.050 --> 00:43:04.640 align:middle line:84%
and you're not going
to combat that.

00:43:04.640 --> 00:43:06.430 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: This is only
going to get worse, though.

00:43:06.430 --> 00:43:08.055 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: You can
combat it by actually

00:43:08.055 --> 00:43:11.420 align:middle line:84%
putting some smart tech in your
computer in the first place.

00:43:11.420 --> 00:43:14.960 align:middle line:84%
And you can train people not
to follow links willy-nilly.

00:43:14.960 --> 00:43:16.130 align:middle line:90%
You get an email.

00:43:16.130 --> 00:43:19.460 align:middle line:84%
You get an email purporting to
be from PayPal, for example.

00:43:19.460 --> 00:43:22.370 align:middle line:84%
And it says, there's a
problem with your account.

00:43:22.370 --> 00:43:23.810 align:middle line:90%
You need to reset your password.

00:43:23.810 --> 00:43:24.610 align:middle line:90%
Click this button.

00:43:24.610 --> 00:43:27.160 align:middle line:90%
Reset your password.

00:43:27.160 --> 00:43:28.823 align:middle line:90%
[CHUCKLES] Well, don't.

00:43:28.823 --> 00:43:30.740 align:middle line:84%
Look at the email address
that it's come from.

00:43:30.740 --> 00:43:32.532 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Always look
at the email address.

00:43:32.532 --> 00:43:35.221 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: Because it
may say, PayPal 7238.

00:43:35.221 --> 00:43:37.090 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Dot IA or
dot whatever, yeah.

00:43:37.090 --> 00:43:38.480 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: There's nothing
like that in PayPal.

00:43:38.480 --> 00:43:39.320 align:middle line:90%
So don't follow it.

00:43:39.320 --> 00:43:41.765 align:middle line:84%
And then go and put your
cursor over any links.

00:43:41.765 --> 00:43:43.640 align:middle line:84%
And hopefully, the link
address will come up.

00:43:43.640 --> 00:43:45.100 align:middle line:90%
And it doesn't say paypal.com.

00:43:45.100 --> 00:43:45.470 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Anywhere.

00:43:45.470 --> 00:43:46.512 align:middle line:90%
>>PEARCE: Don't go there.

00:43:46.512 --> 00:43:51.220 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So maybe a career for
up and coming computer techies

00:43:51.220 --> 00:43:54.460 align:middle line:84%
is really, cybersecurity sounds
like that's where it's at across

00:43:54.460 --> 00:43:58.325 align:middle line:84%
the board, every level of
cybersecurity, from grandma to--

00:43:58.325 --> 00:44:00.950 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: I wouldn't want to be
in that level of cybersecurity,

00:44:00.950 --> 00:44:02.700 align:middle line:84%
because it's such a
game of cat and mouse.

00:44:02.700 --> 00:44:04.820 align:middle line:90%
It's constantly changing.

00:44:04.820 --> 00:44:07.370 align:middle line:84%
Someone is already one step
ahead of you the whole time,

00:44:07.370 --> 00:44:08.780 align:middle line:90%
and you're playing catch-up.

00:44:08.780 --> 00:44:09.530 align:middle line:90%
And then you're going to get--

00:44:09.530 --> 00:44:10.822 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Sounded like an idea.

00:44:10.822 --> 00:44:12.710 align:middle line:90%
What about DuckDuckGo?

00:44:12.710 --> 00:44:13.510 align:middle line:90%
>>PEARCE: DotDotGo?

00:44:13.510 --> 00:44:14.385 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: DuckDuckGo.

00:44:14.385 --> 00:44:15.440 align:middle line:90%
>>PEARCE: Oh, DuckDuckGo.

00:44:15.440 --> 00:44:16.520 align:middle line:90%
I like DuckDuckGo.

00:44:16.520 --> 00:44:18.110 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Because
that's what I use.

00:44:18.110 --> 00:44:19.740 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: I like it mostly
because I like the name.

00:44:19.740 --> 00:44:20.823 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, it's cute.

00:44:20.823 --> 00:44:23.660 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: But it's a browser,
for those that don't know,

00:44:23.660 --> 00:44:27.308 align:middle line:84%
that when you close that
browser down, boom, everything--

00:44:27.308 --> 00:44:28.350 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Like incognito.

00:44:28.350 --> 00:44:30.400 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: Just like incognito,
but slightly more sophisticated.

00:44:30.400 --> 00:44:31.200 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:44:31.200 --> 00:44:34.910 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: And the search
facility is particularly good.

00:44:34.910 --> 00:44:36.950 align:middle line:84%
Supposing you're
a budding author,

00:44:36.950 --> 00:44:39.332 align:middle line:84%
and you want to write a
novel about a terrorist.

00:44:39.332 --> 00:44:41.040 align:middle line:84%
And you want to know
how to build a bomb.

00:44:41.040 --> 00:44:41.860 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And you don't
want to be arrested.

00:44:41.860 --> 00:44:42.180 align:middle line:90%
[CHUCKLES]

00:44:42.180 --> 00:44:42.980 align:middle line:90%
>>PEARCE: No.

00:44:42.980 --> 00:44:46.670 align:middle line:84%
If you start researching "how
do I build a bomb" on Google,

00:44:46.670 --> 00:44:49.800 align:middle line:90%
someone will find out about it.

00:44:49.800 --> 00:44:51.860 align:middle line:84%
You might never know,
but you might never

00:44:51.860 --> 00:44:53.760 align:middle line:90%
be able to get on a plane again.

00:44:53.760 --> 00:44:55.680 align:middle line:84%
Or maybe you can't
access your bank account.

00:44:55.680 --> 00:44:58.800 align:middle line:90%
So this happens a lot.

00:44:58.800 --> 00:44:59.825 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:44:59.825 --> 00:45:01.180 align:middle line:90%
OK, so that's good.

00:45:01.180 --> 00:45:02.410 align:middle line:90%
So we've got incognito.

00:45:02.410 --> 00:45:03.580 align:middle line:90%
We've got DuckDuckGo.

00:45:03.580 --> 00:45:06.600 align:middle line:84%
Those are a couple of easy
ones anybody can access.

00:45:06.600 --> 00:45:10.410 align:middle line:84%
And then as far as any
of the deeper, darker web

00:45:10.410 --> 00:45:12.390 align:middle line:84%
stuff, we probably,
as individuals,

00:45:12.390 --> 00:45:14.890 align:middle line:84%
don't need to go as deeply
as you went into it.

00:45:14.890 --> 00:45:17.015 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: What I would
recommend, though, is people

00:45:17.015 --> 00:45:18.667 align:middle line:84%
get a Virtual Private
Network, a VPN.

00:45:18.667 --> 00:45:19.500 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK, a VPN.

00:45:19.500 --> 00:45:21.790 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: They're
largely inexpensive.

00:45:21.790 --> 00:45:27.760 align:middle line:84%
And people then don't know where
you are, for example, which is--

00:45:27.760 --> 00:45:30.010 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: They can't tell
where you are location-wise.

00:45:30.010 --> 00:45:30.370 align:middle line:90%
>>PEARCE: No.

00:45:30.370 --> 00:45:31.120 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That's a good idea.

00:45:31.120 --> 00:45:32.495 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: So just
supposing I was

00:45:32.495 --> 00:45:36.310 align:middle line:84%
researching how to build a
bomb for a novel I was writing.

00:45:36.310 --> 00:45:38.110 align:middle line:90%
I would have a VPN.

00:45:38.110 --> 00:45:41.460 align:middle line:84%
I'd set it up somewhere
as if I was in Ukraine.

00:45:41.460 --> 00:45:45.220 align:middle line:90%
I would use maybe DuckDuckGo.

00:45:45.220 --> 00:45:47.680 align:middle line:10%
Or if I really
wanted to go deeper,

00:45:47.680 --> 00:45:51.570 align:middle line:10%
I would use the Tor browser,
T-O-R, stands for The Onion

00:45:51.570 --> 00:45:53.440 align:middle line:10%
Router, freely downloadable.

00:45:53.440 --> 00:45:54.880 align:middle line:10%
That puts you in the dark web.

00:45:54.880 --> 00:45:55.680 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:45:55.680 --> 00:45:58.610 align:middle line:10%
>>PEARCE: Right, and then what
with the VPN, what with that,

00:45:58.610 --> 00:46:01.780 align:middle line:10%
and you're bouncing off other
people all around the planet,

00:46:01.780 --> 00:46:04.330 align:middle line:10%
they never trace you back,
unless you're foolish

00:46:04.330 --> 00:46:05.930 align:middle line:10%
and you stay on there too long.

00:46:05.930 --> 00:46:07.810 align:middle line:84%
Or maybe your VPN
dies because there's

00:46:07.810 --> 00:46:10.130 align:middle line:84%
an interruption on the
power supply or something.

00:46:10.130 --> 00:46:11.000 align:middle line:90%
Keep moving.

00:46:11.000 --> 00:46:11.570 align:middle line:90%
Keep moving.

00:46:11.570 --> 00:46:11.990 align:middle line:90%
Keep moving.

00:46:11.990 --> 00:46:13.340 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So all
this is in your book.

00:46:13.340 --> 00:46:14.830 align:middle line:10%
>>PEARCE: All of
this is in the book,

00:46:14.830 --> 00:46:16.538 align:middle line:10%
in the Sherlock Holmes
one because that's

00:46:16.538 --> 00:46:17.755 align:middle line:10%
what they're up against.

00:46:17.755 --> 00:46:19.880 align:middle line:10%
And there's other terrible
things that will happen.

00:46:19.880 --> 00:46:21.617 align:middle line:10%
I talked to Rathik.

00:46:21.617 --> 00:46:23.950 align:middle line:84%
I mean, do you want me to
tell you more horrible things?

00:46:23.950 --> 00:46:24.700 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:46:24.700 --> 00:46:26.825 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Let's to do that
in a second conversation

00:46:26.825 --> 00:46:28.880 align:middle line:84%
because we're out of
time, I'm sorry to say.

00:46:28.880 --> 00:46:29.900 align:middle line:84%
>>PEARCE: Well, we
could talk forever.

00:46:29.900 --> 00:46:31.240 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: We could
talk forever, and I

00:46:31.240 --> 00:46:33.320 align:middle line:84%
